page.title: 17PARISH DETAILS CONTINED
page.content: The earliest scene's of paintings are of the life of St. James. {The chuch {at Stoke Orchard}seems to have been neglected during Victorian times and escaped the "restoration" of those times. Up to that time many more churches has plastered walls. Both churches have Norman arches and doorways. In Tredington church there are fossil remain's in the floor of the porch. It is possible that it is the bones of a marine reptile of the Jurrasic period. If so the bones are 175 million years old. People used to say that it is a fossil ichthyosaurus, but, as it is in pieces, we can't really say that.
